{
  "article_id": "Harrington1928",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "OWNERSHIP BY "
      },
      {
        "text": "CAPT. GEORGE C. NIDEVER",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Capt. George C. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " came into possession of the property in 1840 or 1841. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " came to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1834 from "
      },
      {
        "text": "West Virginia",
        "entity_key": "st_wv",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", having taken eight years to cross the continent, hunting, trapping and fighting by turn. At "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " he followed otter hunting by profession. He was the first man to stock "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He was the principal in the rescue of the \""
      },
      {
        "text": "lone woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "\" of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He married "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sinforosa Sanchez",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1841. Slow of speech and movement, of unblushing integrity, and a dead shot, he was a terror of evildoers. He resided at "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mound",
        "entity_key": "ci_burtons",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for some 10 years and added two outbuildings to the adobe house; one was used as a warehouse for furs, the other as a gristmill. It is said that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " made improvements in the grounds, setting out trees and gardens. To the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Bancroft Library",
        "entity_key": "bancroft",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "University of California",
        "entity_key": "in_ucb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "we are indebted for the following excerpts from a manuscript entitled \"Life and Adventures of George Nidever, Recollections furnished by himself to E. F. Murray for the Bancroft Library, 1878.\" In this interview "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " tells of his purchase of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mound property",
        "entity_key": "ci_burtons",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Joseph Chapman",
        "entity_key": "jchap",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1840, and of his hiding out in the old adobe house on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mound",
        "entity_key": "ci_burtons",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " at the time of the invasion of "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " by the Americans. He says: I was born in 1802, Dec. 20, in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Sul[l]ivan Co.",
        "entity_key": "co_sul",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "East Tenn.",
        "entity_key": "re_etenn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "My father",
        "entity_key": "gnis",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", also named George, was a native of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Penn.",
        "entity_key": "st_penn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "; I do not remember the town. . . . In the fall of 1840 I bought what is now known as the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Burton Mound",
        "entity_key": "ci_burtons",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " property from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Joseph Chapman",
        "entity_key": "jchap",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who had purchased it from the mission. It had formerly been used to store hides in by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ]
  ]
}